uniol.apt.util

Class DebugUtil

  • java.lang.Object
    • uniol.apt.util.DebugUtil

  • public final class DebugUtil
extends java.lang.Object
    Helper functions for having debug output. This class provides a debug() method which can be called with any number of arguments. These arguments are converted to strings, concatenated and printed. For example, you can statically import the debug method and do this: 
     
 debug("Done with step ", step, " after ", time, " seconds");
    The reason for doing things like this is to avoid the overhead of string concatenation if it is not necessary.
    Author:
    Uli Schlachter

      • debugFormat

        public static void debugFormat(java.lang.String format,
                               java.lang.Object... args)
        Generate a formatted debug message if debugging output is enabled. The arguments are passed to String.format(java.lang.String, java.lang.Object...) and the result is printed with a newline appended.
        Parameters:
        format - The format string
        args - Formatting arguments
        See Also:
        String.format(java.lang.String, java.lang.Object...)
